<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-02T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-02T13:00:00-05:00" n="231" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">632.6231/61: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-02T15:00:00-03:00">June 2, 1936—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 2—2:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>141. Department’s 80 June 1, 7 p.m. I saw Macedo this morning, read to
                            him the <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> and at his request left with
                            him a copy. He is to see the President on the subject this
                            afternoon.</p>
                        <p>I expect to see the Minister of Finance later in the day.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>